  "instructions": [
    "Season red snapper fillet with salt, then pat dry with paper towels.",
    "In a pan, heat 1 tbsp olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Sauté onion and garlic for 2 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add ginger and red chili, cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in tomato, lemon juice, coconut milk, and basil; simmer for 5 minutes.",
    "Place red snapper fillet in the pan and cook for 5-7 minutes on each side until cooked through.",
    "Serve hot with a sprinkle of fresh basil and a drizzle of olive oil.",
    "Optional: Add a pinch of black pepper for extra flavor."
